# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FINSIGHT - ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES TEMPLATE
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Fill in your actual Supabase credentials
# 3. DO NOT commit .env.local to git
# 4. DO NOT share these credentials with others
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (REQUIRED)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Get these from: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
#

# Your Supabase project URL
# Format: https://your-project-id.supabase.co
# Example: https://arnzinkozxycyoebttjq.supabase.co
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Supabase public/anonymous key (use for client-side)
# This is the "anon" key from the API settings
# Example: eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-here-starting-with-eyJ

# ALTERNATIVE: If using NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY instead
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY=your-publishable-key-here

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# APPLICATION CONFIGURATION
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Application URL fallback used when browser origin is unavailable.
# In normal browser auth flows, the app now prefers window.location.origin.
# Development: http://localhost:3000
# Production: https://your-domain.com
NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Node environment
# Options: development | production | test
NODE_ENV=development

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# OPTIONAL: ADVANCED CONFIGURATION
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#

# API request timeout (in milliseconds)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# Enable debug mode (logs to console)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEBUG=false

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# 1. CREATE SUPABASE PROJECT:
#    - Go to https://supabase.com
#    - Sign up or log in
#    - Create new project (free tier is fine)
#
# 2. GET YOUR CREDENTIALS:
#    - Click your project name
#    - Settings → API (left sidebar)
#    - Copy "Project URL" → NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#    - Copy "anon" key → NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#
# 3. CONFIGURE DATABASE:
#    - Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor
#    - New Query
#    - Copy entire content of: scripts/initializeSupabase.sql
#    - Paste into SQL editor and run
#    - Wait for completion (~30 seconds)
#
# 4. SEED TEST DATA:
#    - Supabase Dashboard → SQL Editor → New Query
#    - Copy entire content of: scripts/seedTestData.sql
#    - Paste and run
#    - Test data now available in your database
#
# 5. CONFIGURE AUTHENTICATION:
#    - Supabase Dashboard → Authentication (left sidebar)
#    - Go to "Providers" tab
#    - Enable "Email" (toggle ON)
#    - (Optional) Enable Google OAuth:
#      • Get credentials from Google Cloud Console
#      • Paste into Supabase settings
#
# 6. CONFIGURE REDIRECT URL:
#    - Supabase Dashboard → Authentication → URL Configuration
#    - Click "Add a redirect URL"
#    - Enter: http://localhost:3001/auth/callback
#    - Enter: http://localhost:3001/auth/reset-password
#    - For production, add your domain URLs
#
# 7. CREATE .env.local:
#    - Copy this file: cp .env.example .env.local
#    - Replace placeholder values with your credentials
#    - Save and close
#
# 8. RUN DEVELOPMENT SERVER:
#    - npm run dev
#    - Open http://localhost:3001
#    - Sign up with email or Google
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECURITY NOTES
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# PUBLIC KEYS (OK to expose):
# ✅ NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
# ✅ NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY (anonymous/public key)
# ✅ NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY
#
# PRIVATE KEYS (KEEP SECRET):
# 🔒 Service Role Key (never use in frontend)
# 🔒 Session tokens
# 🔒 Password reset tokens
#
# BEST PRACTICES:
# • Never commit .env.local to version control
# • Use .gitignore to prevent accidental commits
# • Rotate keys periodically in production
# • Use separate projects for dev/staging/production
# • Enable Row-Level Security (RLS) on all tables
# • Regularly audit access logs in Supabase Dashboard
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# Q: "User not authenticated"
# A: Check if .env.local has correct credentials and verify Supabase project
#
# Q: "Cannot connect to Supabase"
# A: Verify NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL starts with https://
#    and ends with supabase.co
#
# Q: "Database tables not found"
# A: Run scripts/initializeSupabase.sql in Supabase SQL Editor
#
# Q: "OAuth redirect failed"
# A: Verify redirect URL in Supabase Authentication → URL Configuration
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
